  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">John Anderson came with William Lloyd Garrison on Saturday and was anxious to raise money to redeem the state pledge. They stopped at Edward Earle&apos;s, a Quaker friend. Earle was cowhided in the street by his cousin, but remained non-resistant and made no attempt to defend himself. Garrison lectured in a Methodist meetinghouse to a more than capacity audience. Garrison writes about his immediate plans.</subfield>
